CORRECT. The patch correctly addresses the core bug by ensuring that every newly discovered adjacent vertex is immediately enqueued for later expansion, rather than deferring enqueuing until the queue is empty. This change prevents the omission of vertices reachable only through non-last pending vertices, which was the root cause of the bug. By removing the unnecessary intermediate list and the conditional check on the queue's emptiness, the BFS traversal now properly explores all reachable vertices in the correct order, preserving the breadth-first nature of the algorithm. This fix aligns with the standard BFS approach and guarantees that all vertices connected to the start vertex are visited, thus resolving the issue described in the bug report.
